summary: This is an FBI ELSUR (Electronic Surveillance) evidence envelope form documenting the chain of custody for an intercept. It appears to be related to a consensual monitoring intercept (possibly telephonic) from March 2003, with various agent signatures for custody transfers.

events.title: Intercept Date
events.description: Date the electronic surveillance/intercept was conducted.

keyFacts: The document is an FBI ELSUR evidence envelope form used to track chain of custody for intercepted evidence.
It indicates a consensual monitoring intercept (CM) took place on March 1, 2003.
The form contains multiple signature blocks documenting custody transfers of the evidence, though the signatories' names are not clearly legible in the provided text.
The case number or identifier appears to be partially redacted or obscured (7d-Mtif\--It3311).
The original medium of the intercept is not specified, but options include magnetic tape, computer disk, or printed material.
